com.cyc.kb.wrapper

Class KbCollectionWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.kb.wrapper.KbObjectWrapper
      • com.cyc.kb.wrapper.KbTermWrapper
        • com.cyc.kb.wrapper.KbCollectionWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KbCollection, KbObject, KbObject.KbObjectWithArity, KbTerm
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FirstOrderCollectionWrapper, SecondOrderCollectionWrapper

    public abstract class KbCollectionWrapper
extends KbTermWrapper
implements KbCollection
    An abstract base class for implementing KbCollections per the decorator pattern. To use, extend this class and implement the wrapped() method to return the wrapped object.

      • addGeneralizationSentence

        public Sentence addGeneralizationSentence(KbCollection moreGeneral)
                                   throws KbTypeException,
                                          CreateException
        Description copied from interface: KbCollection
        This method returns the Sentence (#$genls this moreGeneral). The key difference between this and KbCollection.addGeneralization(com.cyc.kb.KbCollection) is that, this method does not make any assertion in the KB. The sentence form of the assertion is generally useful when seeking user feedback before asserting into the KB. Use Sentence.assertIn(com.cyc.kb.Context) to assert the sentence in a Context.
        Specified by:
        addGeneralizationSentence in interface KbCollection
        Parameters:
        moreGeneral - the generalization of this
        Returns:
        the #$genls sentence between this and moreGeneral
        Throws:
        KbTypeException
        CreateException
